{
  "texts": [
    "A number of studies (Rahman and Han, 2017; Zuraimi et al., 2017; Arendt et al., 2018; Wei et al., 2022) employ ML methods to map the CO 2 concentration and occupancy.",
    "Finally, studies such as Zou et al. (2019) propose sensor fusion, where data from multiple sensing modalities, i.e., RGB camera, and Wi-Fi, are used in tandem to come up with a robust activity detection mechanism.",
    "Many of the sensors used for occupancy and activity detection are spatial in nature, i.e., their data are specific to the design of the spatial environment that they are deployed in.",
    "Hence, ML algorithms designed for one environment fails to perform optimally for new environments.",
    "Hence, transfer learning methods have been proposed in the literature to adapt ML models across domains and sensor choices."
  ]
}